    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** anchors the Zurich Zebras with an elite 76.96 efficiency score, leveraging a strong dynamic platoon advantage against R. Nelson. Joining him as a high-upside play is **Colt Keith** (66.91), who benefits from a favorable matchup against Rocker. Rocker\u2019s slow delivery remains a critical factor for our SB-weighted strategy, providing **Colt Keith** and **Caleb Durbin**\u2014who earns a 63.88 despite his #9 spot\u2014additional opportunities to capitalize on the basepaths. **Junior Caminero** also projects well (65.85) as he continues to thrive in his #3 spot in the order, offering the most consistent power-hitting profile in today\u2019s lineup.\n\nStrategic decisions for this roster reflect our aggressive prioritization of efficiency over legacy name value. **Chase Meidroth** (47.06) was the most difficult exclusion from the starting nine; while his profile is steady, he fell just short of the efficiency floor established by **Dillon Dingler** (46.83), who remains in the lineup despite a challenging platoon split due to the high probability of SB opportunities against Rocker. We are also closely monitoring the matchup for **Yordan Alvarez** (53.88), whose score is suppressed by a tough draw against Early (2.97 xERA) and an unfavorable L/L platoon, though his elite 0.434 xwOBA keeps him as a viable UTIL start. With **Christian Yelich**, **Zac Veen**, and **Lars Nootbaar** unavailable due to injury or roster status, the Zebras must rely on this depth to navigate the high-leverage spots effectively, keeping a watchful eye on any late-game weather fluctuations that could impact the offensive environment.",
